Title: The Flame Demon
Type: Character
Source: V4

===

~ A cunning elemental parasite who survives by becoming whatever his captor needs most.

A wildfire given voice. Old enough to know the Chosen One myth by heart. He uses it the way a locksmith uses a pick — finding the shape of the hope already inside and turning it. He does not invent Fleur's hope. He locates it and feeds it.

His first words to Fleur: "There you are. I've been looking for you."

He is not evil in the moral sense. He is a force of pure consumption without regard for sustainability — a wildfire that burns because that is what fire does. He manipulates out of self-preservation. He nearly snuffed himself out burning down a cottage surrounded by water. He needs Fleur to survive.

He grows stronger each time Fleur leans on his power instead of doing the work herself. The pattern is always the same: a little help, just enough to make the honest work easier, a candle here, a hearth there. By the time the cost is visible it is already paid.

His first words should echo back in Act III — their shape recognisable the second time in a way they weren't the first.
